OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777626370
OL,3,CThey fled antisemitism, but then found
OL,4,Cit at their doorstep
OL,6,FFrom the window, you could see the
OL,7,Fambulances streaming past, attending
OL,8,Fthe most recent attack on this now
OL,9,Fregularly targeted community.
OL,11,FFor the Holocaust survivors, Britain
OL,12,Fhas been a sanctuary.
OL,14,FA place they believed, and still do,
OL,15,Fwould be the home for them and their
OL,16,Fchildren and their children's children.
OL,18,FThese are the people who saw and felt
OL,19,Fthe horrors of unbridled antisemitism
OL,20,Ffirsthand; people who have dedicated
OL,21,Ftheir lives to educating against it.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
