PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777626370
OL,3,CThey fled antisemitism, but then found
OL,4,Cit at their doorstep
OL,6,FYet they've seen it rear its head
OL,7,Fagain - this time on UK streets.
OL,9,F"For me, Britain is a place, a safe
OL,10,Fhaven," Susan Pollack, who survived
OL,11,FAuschwitz, said.
OL,13,F"And then such a thing should happen
OL,14,Fis beyond expectation."
OL,16,FEven amongst those who lived through
OL,17,Fthe horrors of the Holocaust, there is
OL,18,Fa deep sense of shock at what happened
OL,19,Fin Golders Green; scenes of Jewish
OL,20,Fpeople being hunted by a man armed
OL,21,Fwith a knife.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
